║                    ARMORED DIVISION FIELD GUIDE                  ║
║                M1A4 "WAR PIG" MAIN BATTLE TANK                  ║
║                     COMMANDER'S REFERENCE                       ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

[VEHICLE STATISTICS]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Crew:           4 (Commander, Driver, Gunner, Loader)
Main Armament:  120mm M256E1 Smoothbore Cannon
                 - APFSDS (Armor-Piercing)  : 14 rounds
                 - HEAT (Anti-Personnel)    : 8 rounds
                 - Canister (CQB Defense)   : 4 rounds
Secondary:      .50 Cal M2 Browning (Commander's Hatch)
                M240 Coaxial 7.62mm (Turret)
Countermeasures: Trophy APS Mk.II, Smoke Dischargers (6x)
Armor:          Chobham-Dorchester Composite + ERA Panels

[WEAK POINTS - CLASSIFIED]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
REAR ARMOR:   Significantly thinner. RPG strikes here are lethal.
              Maintain infantry support to cover rear arc.
TREADS:       Vulnerable to anti-tank mines and RPG-7 volleys.
              Mobility kill = mission kill. Avoid narrow streets.
TURRET RING:  Precision shot location. 2% hit probability but
              catastrophic if penetrated. Keep turret moving.
TOP ARMOR:    Susceptible to Javelin top-attack missiles.
              Urban canyons reduce this threat vector by 70%.

[ENGAGEMENT DOCTRINE]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VS. INFANTRY:   Canister round, 50m lethal radius. Devastating.
                Do not engage beyond 200m with main gun. Waste.
VS. LIGHT ARMOR: HEAT round. Single shot disable. Double tap kill.
VS. ENEMY MBT:   APFSDS. Aim center mass. Lead moving targets.
                 Against T-90: Target lower glacis plate.
VS. AIR THREATS: Evasive maneuvers, smoke screen, call for AA.
                 Trophy APS does NOT intercept aerial bombs.

[URBAN SURVIVAL TACTICS]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1. NEVER advance without infantry screening
2. Rotate 360° scan every 15 seconds in hostile zones
3. Prioritize RPG troopers as immediate threats
4. Use buildings as cover, but avoid rubbling your escape route
5. Thermal optics can see through smoke—use this aggressively

